# Markdown Standards (markdownlint-based)

Follow these markdownlint-inspired rules for consistent Markdown formatting:

## Essential Rules

- **Headings**: Use ATX style with space after hash (`# Heading`)
- **Line length**: Keep lines under 80 characters
- **Blank lines**: Surround headings and code blocks with blank lines
- **Lists**: Use `-` for unordered lists, consistent indentation
- **Links**: Use `[text](url)` format, no bare URLs
- **Code blocks**: Use fenced blocks with language specification
- **No hard tabs**: Use spaces for indentation
- **No multiple blanks**: Maximum one consecutive blank line

## Common Patterns

```markdown
# Document Title

## Section

- List item
- Another item

```python
def example():
    return "code"
```

[Link text](https://example.com)
```

## Key markdownlint Rules

- MD018: Space after ATX heading
- MD013: Line length limit
- MD022: Blank lines around headings  
- MD040: Language in fenced code blocks
- MD010: No hard tabs
- MD012: No multiple blank lines
- MD011: Proper link format
- MD034: No bare URLs 
